TRUE_CONDITION

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Range<Boolean> TRUE_CONDITION

resources

static final ResourceBundle resources

CHECK_CONSISTENCY

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> CHECK_CONSISTENCY
If true, the libSBML model consistency check is performed and the results are written in the glossary of the model report.

CLEAN_WORKSPACE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> CLEAN_WORKSPACE
If this option is set to true, all temporary files will be deleted after running SBML2LaTeX. In case of PDF creation, for instance, this will cause even the TeX file to be deleted. However, this option can be meaningful to remove all the temporary files created by your system's LaTeX compiler.

FONT_HEADINGS

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<String> FONT_HEADINGS
Allows to select the font of captions and other sans serif text. Default: helvetica

FONT_SIZE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Short> FONT_SIZE
The font size for LaTeX documents.

FONT_TEXT

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<String> FONT_TEXT
Allows to select the font of continuous text. Choosing 'times' is actually not recommended because in some cases equations might not look as nicely as they do when using 'mathptmx'. Default: Times font mathptmx.

LANDSCAPE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> LANDSCAPE
Decides whether to set the LaTeX document in landscape or portrait mode.

MIRIAM_ANNOTATION

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> MIRIAM_ANNOTATION
If true (default), MIRIAM annotations are included into the model report if there are any. This option may require the path to the MIRIAM translation file to be specified.

PAPER_SIZE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<String> PAPER_SIZE
The paper size for LaTeX documents.

PRINT_NAMES_IF_AVAILABLE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> PRINT_NAMES_IF_AVAILABLE
Decides whether to write the names or the identifiers of NamedSBase object in equations.

TITLE_PAGE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> TITLE_PAGE
Decides whether to create a separate title page instead of a simple heading.

TYPEWRITER

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> TYPEWRITER
Key that decides whether or not identifiers should be written in typewriter font when these occur in mathematical equations.

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> INCLUDE_COMPARTMENTS_SECTION

PRINT_FULL_ODE_SYSTEM

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> PRINT_FULL_ODE_SYSTEM
Allows to print the entire differential equation system for all species instead of generating links to the reactions.

SHOW_PREDEFINED_UNITS

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> SHOW_PREDEFINED_UNITS
If true (default), all predefined unit definitions of SBML are made explicit.

REACTANTS_OVERVIEW_TABLE

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> REACTANTS_OVERVIEW_TABLE
If true, the details (identifier and name) of all reactants, modifiers and products participating in a reaction are listed in one table. By default a separate table is created for each one of the three participant groups including its SBO term.

FONT_TYPEWRITER

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<String> FONT_TYPEWRITER
Selects the font to be used for typewriter text. Default: cmt.

PDF_LaTeX_COMPILER

static final File PDF_LaTeX_COMPILER
The PDF LaTeX compiler of the system. If this is null, the program pdflatex cannot be found.

LOAD_LATEX_COMPILER

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<File> LOAD_LATEX_COMPILER
The path to the LaTeX compiler to generate PDF, DVI or other files from the created LaTeX report file.

CONFIGURATION_FILES

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.OptionGroup<?> CONFIGURATION_FILES
Here you can specify also the location of the LaTeX compiler on your operating system. Previously, this method also allowed the user to specify the location of the SBML2LaTeX logo file, but this one is now included in the JAR and will not depend on the user any more.

REPORT_OPTIONS

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.OptionGroup<Boolean> REPORT_OPTIONS
Configure the layout of the LaTeX reports, what to be included, and if to remove temporary files afterwards.

LAYOUT_OPTIONS

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.OptionGroup<Boolean> LAYOUT_OPTIONS
These options allow you to influence layout and style of the LaTeX report.

TYPOGRAPHICAL_OPTIONS

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.OptionGroup<?> TYPOGRAPHICAL_OPTIONS

CONTENT_OPTIONS

static final de.zbit.util.prefs.OptionGroup<Boolean> CONTENT_OPTIONS
Select sections to be included in the report.
